Package: cointsmall
Type: Package
Title: Cointegration Test for Very Small Samples
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246"))
Description: Implements the cointegration test with structural breaks
    for very small samples following Trinh (2022)
    <https://www.thema.u-cergy.fr/IMG/pdf/2022-01.pdf>. The method
    applies residual-based ADF-type tests to detect cointegration in
    time-series data with as few as twelve observations. Supports up to
    two endogenous structural breaks in the constant (model 'c') or in
    both constant and slope (model 'cs'). Includes automatic lag selection
    via BIC, a combined sequential testing procedure, and simulation-based
    critical values for small samples.
